#: artemis/reporting/modules/orm_injection_detector/template_orm_injection.jinja2:2
msgid "We identified that the following URLs are vulnerable to ORM injection:"
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/orm_injection_detector/template_orm_injection.jinja2:11
msgid ""
"ORM injection: user input is being passed directly to ORM query methods, "
"allowing an attacker to manipulate query logic by appending ORM-specific "
"suffixes (e.g. __startswith, __contains, __gt) to parameter names. This "
"can be used to extract sensitive data from the database by brute-forcing "
"field values character by character."
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/orm_injection_detector/template_orm_injection.jinja2:20
msgid ""
"ORM sensitive field access: the endpoint allows filtering on sensitive "
"fields (such as password hashes or email addresses) through ORM lookup "
"parameters. An attacker can use this to enumerate users or extract "
"password hashes."
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/orm_injection_detector/template_orm_injection.jinja2:33
msgid ""
"ORM injection occurs when user input is passed directly to ORM query "
"methods (e.g. Model.objects.filter(**request.GET) in Django). Even though"
" no raw SQL is written, an attacker can manipulate the query logic to "
"access data they should not be able to see. To fix this, validate and "
"whitelist allowed parameter names before passing them to the ORM."
msgstr ""
